		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">History of Russian animation</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><i>The <b>History of Russian animation</b> is very rich, but is so far a nearly unexplored field for Western <a href="/wiki/Film_theory" title="Film theory">film theory</a> and history. As most of <a href="/wiki/Russia" title="Russia">Russia</a>'s production of animation for <a href="/wiki/Film" title="Film">cinema</a> and <a href="/wiki/Television" title="Television">television</a> was created during <a href="/wiki/Soviet" title="Soviet" class="mw-redirect">Soviet</a> times, it may also be referred to as the <b>History of Soviet animation</b>.</i></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
<tr>
<td>
<div id="toctitle">
