</ul>
<p><a name="In_Popular_Culture" id="In_Popular_Culture"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=History_of_Russian_animation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: In Popular Culture">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">In Popular Culture</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>An episode of <a href="/wiki/The_Simpsons" title="The Simpsons">The Simpsons</a> called <a href="/wiki/Krusty_Gets_Kancelled" title="Krusty Gets Kancelled">Krusty Gets Kancelled</a> features a parody of Soviet animation, a cat and mouse duo known as Worker and Parasite. The show's creater <a href="/wiki/Matt_Groening" title="Matt Groening">Matt Groening</a> has stated that Worker and Parasite is one of his favourite moments in The Simpsons history.</li>
<li>The Irish comedy act Diet Of Worms created a series of short animations in the early Soviet style known as <a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Adventures_Of_Puffincat&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="The Adventures Of Puffincat (page does not exist)">The Adventures Of Puffincat</a>. The cartoons are narrated by a man speaking in a heavily exaggerated Russian accent.</li>
</ul>
